16/01/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- At their session Tuesday (January 15th), lawmakers agreed on the formation of 13 parliamentary committees, each composed of 12 members. The three largest parliamentary parties -- the Democratic Party of Kosovo, the Democratic League of Kosovo and the Alliance New Kosovo -- will chair three committees each. After the session, Parliament Speaker Jakup Krasniqi said work is continuing on a constitution, state symbols and a draft for the date on which Kosovo declares independence.
Meanwhile, new Prime Minister Hashim Thaci will participate in Wednesday's UN Security Council debate on Kosovo. Libya, which recently took the helm of the council, has accepted Thaci's request to address the council regarding the current situation in Kosovo and future plans. (RTK, QIK, Kosovalive - 15/01/08)
